  "description": [
    "Navys Blue Angels Seek New Members The Navys Flight Demonstra tion Team the Blue Angels is considering applications for new members Two very important billets will be filled within the next few months They are those of the teams Public Information Officer and the Maintenance Of ficer Maintenance Officer The Maintenance Officer is re sponsible for maintaining the Blue Angels six F11F Tigers and the F9F8T Cougar on a 100 per cent availability status He flies about 600 hours a year in the teams R5D and is airborne in the Cougar or Tiger every chance he gets The team has about 50 of the finest Jet mechan ics in the world PlOs Duties The PlOs duties are many and varied While at Pensacola he answers fan mail and handles advance liaison work concerning future appearances In addition he spends approximately 500 hours a year in the groups Cougar normally traveling ahead of the team setting up its schedule flying news media on jet indoctrination rides narrating the Blue Angels shows etc Address Those interested in either of these billets may contact the team by writing LCDR Kenneth R Wallace Officer in Charge Blue Angels NAS Pensacola Florida Foreign Officers Finish"
  ],
